{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nProve the batch write reduces commit count and does not break crash-resume: a before/after\ncommit-count benchmark on a synthetic many-event import, plus rollback + crash-resume tests.\n**Depends on B1 (890d) and B2 (6386)** — the primitive and the importer adoption must exist.\n\n## Why\nBatching changes commit granularity (N events per commit). We must demonstrate the win\n(commit-count reduction) and prove the safety properties: all-or-nothing per commit, and\nthat a crash mid-batch plus the `source_id` re-scan resumes cleanly. NOTE: the importer's\nexisting LINE parsing is fail-open (a malformed NDJSON line is skipped); the whole-chunk\nrollback proven here is a property of the BATCH PRIMITIVE (`batch_stage_and_commit`) — one\nevent that fails validation inside a chunk rolls back that chunk's already-staged events —\nnot of the importer's line parser.\n\n## Scope\n- Benchmark test: build a synthetic N=3000 NDJSON where each ticket has 1 CREATE + 1 comment\n  and no parents/file-impact/verify/links/statuses (so only Pass 1 and Pass 2d carry events),\n  run `import_tickets`, and assert the commit-count DELTA (`int(subprocess.run([\"git\",\"-C\",\n  tracker,\"rev-list\",\"--count\",\"HEAD\"],capture_output=True,text=True).stdout)` after − before)\n  == `2*ceil(3000/256)` (=24), >=10x fewer than the ~6000 per-event commits.\n- Malformed-event-mid-chunk test (batch primitive level): a chunk containing one event that\n  fails `_validate_event` triggers whole-chunk rollback — index clean, no partial commit,\n  no phantom staged blob.\n- Crash-resume test: simulate a crash before a chunk's `git commit` (e.g. monkeypatch the\n  commit to raise after staging); assert the store is left whole-commit-or-none, then re-run\n  the import and assert the `source_id` re-scan skips committed events and re-emits the rest.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Benchmark test asserts the commit-count DELTA (`git rev-list --count HEAD` after − before; baseline `init_repo` commits excluded via the delta) == `2*ceil(3000/256)` (=24) for a synthetic N=3000 CREATE+comment import, >=10x fewer than the ~6000 per-event commits\n- [ ] Malformed-event-mid-chunk test: a chunk containing an event dict that fails the primitive's validation (invalid `event_type` / missing `uuid`) rolls the whole chunk back — `git diff --cached --name-only` empty, no partial commit, no phantom staged blob\n- [ ] Crash-resume test: monkeypatch `event_append.subprocess.run` so `git commit` succeeds for the first K 256-chunks then raises after staging on chunk K+1. Assert (i) whole-commit-or-none at the failing chunk: `git diff --cached --name-only` is empty (B1's rollback ran) and the committed ticket count == exactly K*256 (no partial chunk); then undo the monkeypatch and re-run the same import and assert (ii) `rebar.list_tickets` returns every source ticket exactly once (no duplicates/losses), and (iii) the re-run adds only `ceil((N-K*256)/256)`-worth of new commits — proving the source_id re-scan skipped the already-committed K chunks (compare `git rev-list --count HEAD` before/after the re-run)\n- [ ] Named regression suites green (verified paths): `tests/unit/test_store_batch_write.py`, `tests/interfaces/store/test_reducer_single_source.py` + `tests/unit/test_reducer_status_fork_record.py` (replay), `tests/unit/test_sync_union_recovery.py` + `tests/interfaces/store/test_gitattributes_merge.py` (union-merge convergence), `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_compact_negative.py` + `tests/unit/test_repo_snapshot.py` + `tests/unit/test_snapshot_cache.py` (SNAPSHOT compaction)\n- [ ] `make test` green"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783658133707257001,"uuid":"7cc11f4b-93a2-4744-95d0-5894c575a25f"}